Colours have changed!!

Rating the speed of various macOS #RStats interactive graphics devices on a particular multiframe test case:

* Rstudio "Plots" pane: 3 fps
* quartz(): 12 fps
* x11(): 11 fps
* x11(type='cairo'): 19fps

Summary: the Rstudio viewer pane is slooooooow

Note: This bug is only for "x11(type = 'Xlib')" (the default).

If you specify the device as "x11(type = 'cairo')" then the colours are all OK.

The 'cairo' variant of 'x11()' is about twice as fast as the 'Xlib' variant anyways, so this now becomes a non-issue for me
